31/03/2008
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Defence Minister Vesselin Bliznakov told public radio Sunday (March 30th) that Bulgaria supports the NATO bids of Macedonia, Croatia and Albania. 
"It is very important for us, as a Balkan country, that the three countries ... 
become members of the Alliance," Bliznakov said. 
Their bids will be discussed at NATO's summit in Bucharest, which begins on Wednesday. 
Bulgaria joined NATO in 2004. 
(Makfax - 31/03/08; BNR, DPA - 30/03/08)
